        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 7:16PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 715 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Mena to near Octavia to 8 miles northeast
of Nashoba. Movement was south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Plunketville, Smithville, Watson, Bethel, Battiest, Pickens, Mount
Herman, and Sherwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
